    <html:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called a <html:em><html:strong>set</html:strong></html:em> when for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</html:p>
