                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called a <html:em><html:strong>set</html:strong></html:em> when for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <html:p>The notions of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositional</fr:link> types generate an infinite hierarchy of <html:em>truncation levels</html:em> expressing the point after which higher identifications become trivial.</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001F</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001F.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Indexing of truncation levels">Indexing of truncation levels</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Convention</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001F.agda" type="external">erct-001F.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>truncation level</html:strong></html:em> is an integer <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  -2]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001G</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001G.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="n-truncated type"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> type</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>Given a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001F.xml" title="Indexing of truncation levels" addr="forest://erct/erct-001F" type="local">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> by induction:</html:p>
                <html:ul><html:li>a type is <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-2]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when it is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>a type is <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when it is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>;</html:li>
  <html:li>for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, a type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> is <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span>.</html:li></html:ul>
                <html:p>So, in particular, a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>-truncated type is precisely a <html:em>set</html:em>. We shall often refer to <html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> types as <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-types</html:span></html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001T</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="n-truncated map"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> map</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em><html:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></html:strong></html:em> when all of its <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fibers</fr:link> are <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> types</fr:link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <html:em><html:strong>contractible</html:strong></html:em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <html:em><html:strong>propositional</html:strong></html:em> when their fibers are <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositions</fr:link>.</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" hidden-when-empty="true">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors />
        <fr:title text="Backlinks">Backlinks</fr:title>
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-001N/0</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001N/0.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Being contractible is a proposition › "><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001N.xml" title="Being contractible is a proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001N" type="local">Being <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a,a':A]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _\bullet \colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}a = x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi '_\bullet \colon \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}a'=x]]></fr:tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen a,\chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 with 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen a',\chi '_\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, we employ the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0035.xml" title="Covariant sum of a left-cloven family of path objects" addr="forest://erct/erct-0035" type="local">covariant sum</fr:link> of each of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001C.xml" title="Dependent product of path objects" addr="forest://erct/erct-001C" type="local">pointwise path object</fr:link> structures on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}-=x]]></fr:tex> over the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0013.xml" title="The intrinsic path object on a type" addr="forest://erct/erct-0013" type="local">intrinsic path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, constructing an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\colon  a = a']]></fr:tex> followed by a homotopy <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H \colon  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \sim  \chi '_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\colon  A]]></fr:tex>, we compute:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}
 z
      &=
      
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*^{-=z} \chi _z
      \\
      &=
      \chi _{a'}^{-1} \cdot  \chi _z
      \\
      &= \chi '_z
    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001J.xml" title="Sets" addr="forest://erct/erct-001J" type="local">set</fr:link>, which we may deduce from <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001K.xml" title="Contractible types are propositions" addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001L.xml" title="Propositions are sets" addr="forest://erct/erct-001L" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001L" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
